article.headline: Florida A&M 76, Edward Waters 61
article.story: TALLAHASSEE, Fla. (AP) -- Darius Glover scored 17 points and added nine rebounds as Florida A&M defeated Edward Waters 76-61 Thursday. The Rattlers outscored the Tigers 42-14 in the paint. Its defense held Edward Waters to 30-percent shooting from the field, and forced 26 turnovers. Brian Greene also finished with 17 points and nine rebounds for the Rattlers (4-5). Greene's highlight reel dunk sparked an 11-2 Rattler to end the half, giving them a 36-25 halftime lead. Glover's eleven second half points paced the Rattlers, who led the entire game. Rome Sanders also had 15 points, and L.C. Robinson scored eleven, but the Rattlers turned the ball over 27 times. Edward Waters' Bobby Brown led the way for the Tigers (5-6), finishing with 15 points and 13 rebounds before fouling out. Edward Waters also got 14 points from Edward Turner, and Jeffrey Wimbush scored ten points and pulled down eight rebounds.
